# Styling with Tailwind CSS

This project uses Tailwind CSS for styling with some additional plugins and customizations.

## Key Files

- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind configuration
- [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global CSS styles
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - shadcn/ui component configuration

## Styling Conventions

1. Use Tailwind utility classes for component styling
2. Use shadcn/ui components as building blocks when possible
3. Use CSS variables for theming in [globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
4. For complex components, consider using Tailwind's `@apply` directive
5. Use the `cn()` utility from `src/lib/utils.ts` for conditional class names

## UI Components

The project uses shadcn/ui, a collection of reusable components built on top of Tailwind CSS:

1. UI components are stored in [src/components/ui](mdc:src/components/ui)
2. Follow the component structure from shadcn/ui
3. Use the provided components as building blocks for more complex UI
